Chroma supports filtering queries by metadata and document contents. The where filter is used to filter by metadata.

In order to filter on metadata, you must supply a where filter dictionary to the query. The dictionary must have the following structure:


{
    "metadata_field": {
        <Operator>: <Value>
    }
}

7be5a036-f44c-421a-b991-4502ff156fc9:
# Using the $eq operator is equivalent to using the where filter
{
    "metadata_field": "search_string"
}

# is equivalent to

{
    "metadata_field": {
        "$eq": "search_string"
    }
}

91733155-aced-48e8-bcc1-633e7c4dc063:
# An $and operator will return results that match all of the filters in the list.
{
    "$and": [
        {
            "metadata_field": {
                <Operator>: <Value>
            }
        },
        {
            "metadata_field": {
                <Operator>: <Value>
            }
        }
    ]
}

e9844780-3e02-44bf-8c87-1fc07cacaa9e:
# An $or operator will return results that match any of the filters in the list.
{
    "$or": [
        {
            "metadata_field": {
                <Operator>: <Value>
            }
        },
        {
            "metadata_field": {
                <Operator>: <Value>
            }
        }
    ]
}

